# Available Secrets

When running as a cloud agent or background agent, the following environment secrets should be available. Reference them via process.env or shell $env: variables.

- FTP_HOST - FTP server hostname for 20i hosting
- FTP_USER - FTP username
- FTP_PASS - FTP password
- WP_URL - WordPress site URL (https://land-property-northwest.co.uk)
- WP_ADMIN_USER - WordPress admin username
- WP_ADMIN_PASS - WordPress admin password
- STRIPE_PUBLISHABLE_KEY - Stripe publishable API key
- STRIPE_SECRET_KEY - Stripe secret API key
- MAUTIC_URL - Mautic instance URL
- MAUTIC_USER - Mautic admin username
- MAUTIC_PASS - Mautic admin password
- EPC_API_KEY - EPC Open Data API key

**`LPNW_CRON_SECRET`** — required on production for `?lpnw_cron=tick&key=...` (see `docs/DEPLOYMENT.md`).

**`LPNW_PAGE_SYNC_SECRET`** — optional; used for `?lpnw_update=pages&key=...` when not logged in as admin.

**`LPNW_LOGIN_AS_SECRET`** — use for `lpnw-login-as` / autologin URLs and match `wp-config.php`. Cloud agents should have this in **Cursor environment secrets** so browser automation can append `&key=...`. See `docs/DEPLOYMENT.md`.

**One-shot tools** (`tools/*.php` copied to mu-plugins): `&key=` may match any of the three constants above, or the dev-only fallback `lpnw2026setup` if none are set. `mu-plugins/lpnw-tool-auth-loader.php` defines `lpnw_tool_query_key_ok()` for scripts in that folder.

## FTP Deployment from Agent

To deploy plugin changes via FTP from a cloud agent shell, use PowerShell .NET FTP or install lftp. The plugin uploads to `/public_html/wp-content/plugins/lpnw-property-alerts/` and the theme to `/public_html/wp-content/themes/lpnw-theme/`.
